Spit it out.

1346
01:04:17,360 --> 01:04:18,759
You believe
in demonstrators?

1347
01:04:18,800 --> 01:04:19,869
Huh? What?

1348
01:04:19,920 --> 01:04:22,753
I just don't agree
with everything you're saying.

1349
01:04:22,800 --> 01:04:24,677
I don't think
you understand.

1350
01:04:24,720 --> 01:04:26,597
What does
Tommy know?

1351
01:04:26,640 --> 01:04:28,232
I don't understand?

1352
01:04:28,320 --> 01:04:30,151
He's hanging around
with longhairs

1353
01:04:30,240 --> 01:04:31,832
who take drugs!

1354
01:04:31,880 --> 01:04:33,279
That's not the reason.

1355
01:04:33,320 --> 01:04:34,435
Have they ever worked?

1356
01:04:34,520 --> 01:04:36,670
You want to burn the flag?
Huh, Tommy?

1357
01:04:36,760 --> 01:04:37,875
What is this?

1358
01:04:37,960 --> 01:04:40,349
You want to
bring down this country?

1359
01:04:40,440 --> 01:04:42,715
Love it
or leave it, Tommy.

1360
01:04:42,760 --> 01:04:44,591
All they're
trying to say, Ronnie,

1361
01:04:44,680 --> 01:04:47,035
is they don't
want more people

1362
01:04:47,080 --> 01:04:48,832
to come back like you.

1363
01:04:48,880 --> 01:04:50,199
That's an easy excuse.

1364
01:04:50,280 --> 01:04:53,397
Where were they when
their country needed them?

1365
01:04:53,480 --> 01:04:54,833
You served your country.

1366
01:04:54,920 --> 01:04:57,718
What did you
get out of it?

1367
01:04:57,800 --> 01:04:59,518
Look at you.

1368
01:04:59,560 --> 01:05:02,393
Well, look at me.

1369
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:04,192
Look at you, man.

1370
01:05:04,240 --> 01:05:07,232
I got to go. I'll see
you around, all right?

1371
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:09,157
What's wrong
with me, Tommy?

1372
01:05:09,240 --> 01:05:10,912
What's wrong
with me?

1373
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:12,956
Is there something
wrong with me?

1374
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,353
I volunteered,
Tommy!

1375
01:05:14,440 --> 01:05:17,159
You don't know
what you're talking about!

1376
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:18,599
Were you there?

1377
01:05:18,640 --> 01:05:21,950
You can just love it
or leave it, Tommy!

1378
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:23,393
Mom, I can't believe

1379
01:05:23,440 --> 01:05:25,635
what Tommy just
said to me.

1380
01:05:25,680 --> 01:05:26,715
I can't...

1381
01:05:26,760 --> 01:05:30,275
I can't believe
what Tommy just said to me.

1382
01:05:36,000 --> 01:05:37,228
Parade time, Ronnie.

1383
01:05:37,320 --> 01:05:40,756
You tell them I'll be
right there, all right?

1384
01:05:42,120 --> 01:05:45,112
What kind of car is it?

1385
01:05:45,160 --> 01:05:46,718
I think it's
a Continental.

1386
01:05:46,760 --> 01:05:47,829
Continental?

1387
01:05:47,880 --> 01:05:48,915
A convertible?

1388
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:49,876
Yeah.

1389
01:05:49,960 --> 01:05:51,632
They said
it would be.

1390
01:05:51,720 --> 01:05:53,312
Coming up
in the world.

1391
01:05:57,480 --> 01:05:59,675
Would you like to ride

1392
01:05:59,720 --> 01:06:03,156
In my beautiful balloon

1393
01:06:03,240 --> 01:06:05,356
Would you like to ride

1394
01:06:05,440 --> 01:06:08,477
In my beautiful balloon

1395
01:06:08,520 --> 01:06:11,717
We could float among
the stars together

1396
01:06:11,760 --> 01:06:13,796
You and I

1397
01:06:13,880 --> 01:06:16,997
For we can fly

1398
01:06:17,040 --> 01:06:20,350
We can fly

1399
01:06:20,440 --> 01:06:22,635
Up, up and away

1400
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:24,472
In my beautiful

1401
01:06:24,520 --> 01:06:25,714
My beautiful

1402
01:06:25,800 --> 01:06:31,670
Balloon

1403
01:06:51,520 --> 01:06:52,839
Die!

1404
01:07:38,240 --> 01:07:42,153
Today is July the 4th,
and I believe in America.

1405
01:07:43,640 --> 01:07:45,631
And I believe
in Americanism.

1406
01:07:46,880 --> 01:07:48,233
But most of all,

1407
01:07:48,320 --> 01:07:50,754
I believe in victory
for America.

1408
01:07:52,480 --> 01:07:55,552
Some people are starting
to say the war is wrong,

1409
01:07:55,640 --> 01:07:57,312
that we shouldn't be there.

1410
01:07:57,400 --> 01:08:00,233
Some people would like to
tear our country down.

1411
01:08:00,320 --> 01:08:01,799
But who are the kids

1412
01:08:01,880 --> 01:08:03,711
defending their right
to protest?

1413
01:08:03,800 --> 01:08:05,950
These are the kids
who care about America,

1414
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:08,679
kids who have respect
for their flag

1415
01:08:08,760 --> 01:08:10,910
and their parents
and their government

1416
01:08:11,000 --> 01:08:13,309
and their religion.

1417
01:08:13,400 --> 01:08:15,709
Kids like Joey Walsh.
